Your feelings contain
the wisdom of millions

00:45:57.150 --> 00:45:59.950
upon millions of
years of evolution,

00:45:59.950 --> 00:46:03.210
the algorithms that
are your feelings

00:46:03.210 --> 00:46:08.270
have passed the most rigorous
tests of natural selection.

00:46:08.270 --> 00:46:11.460
Each one of your genes, and
each one of your algorithms

00:46:11.460 --> 00:46:15.310
is here today because it has
succeeded for millions of years

00:46:15.310 --> 00:46:20.150
to pass the most rigorous
tests of natural selection.

00:46:20.150 --> 00:46:23.680
So if you need to
make a decision

00:46:23.680 --> 00:46:26.140
you better go with
your feelings.

00:46:26.140 --> 00:46:30.350
This was the situation
maybe until today.

00:46:30.350 --> 00:46:33.010
But now things are changing.

00:46:33.010 --> 00:46:35.780
In two ways things are changing.

00:46:35.780 --> 00:46:39.400
First of all,
biologists decipher

00:46:39.400 --> 00:46:43.700
the biochemical algorithms
that compose our body

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:46.400
and that are responsible
for our feelings.

00:46:46.400 --> 00:46:49.960
They are no longer mysterious
entities as they were before.

00:46:49.960 --> 00:46:52.600
We understand them
better and better.

00:46:52.600 --> 00:46:56.590
Why I feel this way in
this particular situation.

00:46:56.590 --> 00:46:59.520
And secondly, we have
computer scientists

00:46:59.520 --> 00:47:05.130
that are creating better and
better electronic algorithms.

00:47:05.130 --> 00:47:07.850
Now the question
that arises today

00:47:07.850 --> 00:47:13.130
is what will happen once
we create an algorithm that

00:47:13.130 --> 00:47:15.750
knows me better,
that understands me

00:47:15.750 --> 00:47:21.400
and my feelings better than
I can understand myself?

00:47:21.400 --> 00:47:25.750
What will happen then is
that authority will shift.

00:47:25.750 --> 00:47:30.610
It will shift away from
the feelings of individuals

00:47:30.610 --> 00:47:34.690
to these outside algorithms.

00:47:34.690 --> 00:47:37.500
Our feelings at
present, you can say,

00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:41.280
are the best algorithms
in the universe.

00:47:41.280 --> 00:47:45.280
But after all, they
are becoming outdated.

00:47:45.280 --> 00:47:49.780
They appeared maybe the way
that we have them today maybe

00:47:49.780 --> 00:47:53.710
a few tens of thousands of years
ago in the African Savanna.

00:47:53.710 --> 00:47:56.860
So far they have been the
best algorithms around,

00:47:56.860 --> 00:48:01.330
but we are now at the
position to produce an updated

00:48:01.330 --> 00:48:04.070
version, something better.

00:48:04.070 --> 00:48:05.940
And when we have
better algorithms

00:48:05.940 --> 00:48:08.680
then the authority
will shift to them.

00:48:08.680 --> 00:48:12.350
This is already happening in
at least a few fields of life,

00:48:12.350 --> 00:48:15.940
most clearly in the
field of medicine

00:48:15.940 --> 00:48:20.800
and decisions about your own
body, and your own health.

00:48:20.800 --> 00:48:24.790
I think it's not far fetched
to say that all of you

00:48:24.790 --> 00:48:28.370
are now listening to this
talk, including myself,

00:48:28.370 --> 00:48:32.430
the most important
decisions about our bodies

00:48:32.430 --> 00:48:37.370
during our lifetime will not
to be taken by our feelings.

00:48:37.370 --> 00:48:41.260
They will be taken by
external algorithms,

00:48:41.260 --> 00:48:45.580
algorithms that understand
our own internal systems

00:48:45.580 --> 00:48:47.820
and that have statistics
about millions

00:48:47.820 --> 00:48:50.340
upon millions of other
humans, and therefore

00:48:50.340 --> 00:48:53.930
can make better predictions
and better decisions

00:48:53.930 --> 00:48:58.050
about our bodies than
just my own feelings.

00:48:58.050 --> 00:49:00.420
To give a concrete
example I think

00:49:00.420 --> 00:49:02.870
it was a year ago, two
years ago that this

00:49:02.870 --> 00:49:06.890
is very famous story came
out with Angelina Jolie

00:49:06.890 --> 00:49:10.370
that she had a
double mastectomy.

00:49:10.370 --> 00:49:11.110
Why?

00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:15.030
Not because she discovered
she had breast cancer.

00:49:15.030 --> 00:49:16.620
She didn't have breast cancer.

00:49:16.620 --> 00:49:22.150
But she went and did a
genetic test scanning her DNA.

00:49:22.150 --> 00:49:28.140
And it showed that she carries
a mutation in one of her genes

00:49:28.140 --> 00:49:31.050
that, according to the
statistical database,

00:49:31.050 --> 00:49:36.520
means she has an 87% chance
of getting breast cancer.

00:49:36.520 --> 00:49:39.530
And she had a lot of breast
cancer cases in her family.

00:49:39.530 --> 00:49:42.680
I think that her mother died
at a relatively young age

00:49:42.680 --> 00:49:44.770
from breast cancer.

00:49:44.770 --> 00:49:48.140
She did not have breast
cancer at the time.

00:49:48.140 --> 00:49:50.580
Her feelings told her
nothing, that she is sick,

00:49:50.580 --> 00:49:52.080
that she should do something.

00:49:52.080 --> 00:49:54.680
But the external
algorithms told her

00:49:54.680 --> 00:49:59.470
you have an 87% chance
of getting this disease.

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:01.210
So she had a double
mastectomy, which

00:50:01.210 --> 00:50:05.250
is a very, very big decision
to make in a person's life.

00:50:05.250 --> 00:50:09.670
And likewise I think most of
the big decisions we will make

00:50:09.670 --> 00:50:12.470
about our lives in our
lifetime will actually

00:50:12.470 --> 00:50:15.990
be taken by such
external algorithms,

00:50:15.990 --> 00:50:18.140
not based on our inner feelings.

00:50:21.750 --> 00:50:26.780
Now when this will spread to
more and more fields of life,

00:50:26.780 --> 00:50:31.380
liberalism will collapse,
not necessarily violently,

00:50:31.380 --> 00:50:34.450
but it will simply
become outdated.

00:50:34.450 --> 00:50:39.100
People will move authority
to a different place.

00:50:39.100 --> 00:50:41.800
This has happened
before in history.

00:50:41.800 --> 00:50:46.120
In the transition from the
Middle Ages to the modern age,

00:50:46.120 --> 00:50:50.080
in the Middle Ages at the
time when the dominance was

00:50:50.080 --> 00:50:55.090
of [? faced ?] religions, when
people had faced a decision,

00:50:55.090 --> 00:51:00.460
a problem, the practical
guideline they received

00:51:00.460 --> 00:51:02.870
was listen to scriptures.

00:51:02.870 --> 00:51:05.160
Read what is written
in scriptures.

00:51:05.160 --> 00:51:07.500
This will give you an answer.

00:51:07.500 --> 00:51:12.230
Now the rise of liberalism
was not a theoretical change.

00:51:12.230 --> 00:51:14.600
It was not just a
matter of philosophy.

00:51:14.600 --> 00:51:17.770
It was a practical matter
of how people actually

00:51:17.770 --> 00:51:20.810
make decisions in
their daily lives.

00:51:20.810 --> 00:51:24.930
If previously, when they faced
a problem, say, who to marry,

00:51:24.930 --> 00:51:27.880
they opened scriptures
and looked for the answer.

00:51:27.880 --> 00:51:31.580
Now, with the rise
of liberalism,

00:51:31.580 --> 00:51:34.660
the guidance was listen
to your feelings.

00:51:34.660 --> 00:51:38.070
Go maybe at night,
climb the high mountain.

00:51:38.070 --> 00:51:39.070
Look at the moon.

00:51:39.070 --> 00:51:39.845
Look at the sea.

00:51:39.845 --> 00:51:41.680
Try to connect to yourself.

00:51:41.680 --> 00:51:44.700
See what you really feel
and go with your heart.

00:51:44.700 --> 00:51:45.890
Go with your feelings.

00:51:45.890 --> 00:51:47.990
This was a practical guidance.

00:51:47.990 --> 00:51:50.110
It was not just theory.

00:51:50.110 --> 00:51:52.170
Now we move to the next stage.

00:51:52.170 --> 00:51:54.800
When people say, don't
listen to your feelings,

00:51:54.800 --> 00:51:56.030
what do they know?

00:51:56.030 --> 00:51:58.980
Listen to Google, or listen
to Amazon, or to Facebook,

00:51:58.980 --> 00:51:59.830
or whatever.

00:51:59.830 --> 00:52:03.650
They understand
how you feel better

00:52:03.650 --> 00:52:06.390
than you know how
you feel because they

00:52:06.390 --> 00:52:08.350
have much more information.

00:52:08.350 --> 00:52:10.640
And they have much
better algorithms

00:52:10.640 --> 00:52:13.640
than what natural
selection gave you.

00:52:13.640 --> 00:52:15.920
They have information not
only about your emails

00:52:15.920 --> 00:52:18.820
and your books and so
forth, but the latest rage

00:52:18.820 --> 00:52:23.960
is all these biometric devices
that you wear on your body,

00:52:23.960 --> 00:52:26.880
and that gets a constant
stream of information

00:52:26.880 --> 00:52:30.580
about your blood pressure
and your sugar levels,

00:52:30.580 --> 00:52:31.340
and whatever.

00:52:31.340 --> 00:52:34.570
And, of course, do a DNA test,
and so forth and so forth.

00:52:34.570 --> 00:52:37.610
And if you have all this
information and these superbly

00:52:37.610 --> 00:52:41.430
built algorithms you can
get much better answers

00:52:41.430 --> 00:52:44.630
than from your feelings, or
certainly from the Bible.

00:52:47.470 --> 00:52:50.490
So we see the potential
rise of a new kind

00:52:50.490 --> 00:52:53.010
of religion, a data religion.

00:52:53.010 --> 00:52:57.450
If previously God was in the
center of events and then

00:52:57.450 --> 00:52:59.430
humans were in the
center of events.

00:52:59.430 --> 00:53:03.540
Now data or information
becomes the supreme source

00:53:03.540 --> 00:53:06.550
of authority and of
meaning in the world.

