01:03:17.600 --> 01:03:21.710
caught small animals, and
harvested stuff, and whatever.

01:03:21.710 --> 01:03:27.670
So at what point in human
history did it become uneven?

01:03:27.670 --> 01:03:29.330
YUVAL HARARI: Did
patriarchy arise?

01:03:29.330 --> 01:03:30.550
AUDIENCE: Yes.

01:03:30.550 --> 01:03:33.160
YUVAL HARARI: Well, the
simplest-- I have a thing.

01:03:33.160 --> 01:03:35.720
Do you hear me?

01:03:35.720 --> 01:03:38.930
The simplest answer
is that we don't know.

01:03:38.930 --> 01:03:41.230
One of the things I
like most about science

01:03:41.230 --> 01:03:43.050
is that when we
don't know something,

01:03:43.050 --> 01:03:45.900
we can simply say we don't know.

01:03:45.900 --> 01:03:50.290
We have very little idea
how gender relations were

01:03:50.290 --> 01:03:53.110
prior to the
agricultural revolution.

01:03:53.110 --> 01:03:54.970
After the agricultural
revolution

01:03:54.970 --> 01:03:57.610
when we have in mass
of first archaeological

01:03:57.610 --> 01:04:00.790
and then written
records, we know

01:04:00.790 --> 01:04:02.620
that they were patriarchal.

01:04:02.620 --> 01:04:04.450
Like you see even
10,000 years ago,

01:04:04.450 --> 01:04:07.800
you find the remains of
people from 10,000 years ago,

01:04:07.800 --> 01:04:09.960
after the agricultural
revolution.

01:04:09.960 --> 01:04:14.160
You see that in times of famine
they allowed the girls to die

01:04:14.160 --> 01:04:15.420
and kept the boys.

01:04:15.420 --> 01:04:18.410
The boys were fed-- you see in
skeletons that girls suffered

01:04:18.410 --> 01:04:22.410
far more from malnutrition than
boys in the same community.

01:04:22.410 --> 01:04:25.410
So this is a clear evidence
of patriarchy shortly

01:04:25.410 --> 01:04:27.580
after the agricultural
revolution.

01:04:27.580 --> 01:04:30.840
How did gender relations,
or family structures,

01:04:30.840 --> 01:04:34.370
how did they look like 20,000
years ago, 50,000 years ago?

01:04:34.370 --> 01:04:35.470
There are many theories.

01:04:35.470 --> 01:04:38.650
We have no firm evidence.

01:04:38.650 --> 01:04:43.390
Even if 50,000 years ago there
was a matriarchal society,

01:04:43.390 --> 01:04:46.780
or an egalitarian
society, this is not

01:04:46.780 --> 01:04:49.380
the case in the
last 10,000 years.

01:04:49.380 --> 01:04:52.020
So even if feminism,
the feminist revolution

01:04:52.020 --> 01:04:55.550
returns things to what they
were like 50,000 years ago,

01:04:55.550 --> 01:04:57.380
in terms of the
last 10,000 years,

01:04:57.380 --> 01:05:00.700
it's still probably the
biggest social revolution

01:05:00.700 --> 01:05:02.980
that occurred.

01:05:02.980 --> 01:05:05.900
What is even more
important to realize

01:05:05.900 --> 01:05:10.610
is that not only we don't know
what was the situation 20,000

01:05:10.610 --> 01:05:14.870
years ago, we don't have at
present any good explanation

01:05:14.870 --> 01:05:16.660
for patriarchy.

01:05:16.660 --> 01:05:20.780
Many people think that the
domination of society by men

01:05:20.780 --> 01:05:22.960
and the domination
of women by men

01:05:22.960 --> 01:05:27.430
is obvious because men
are physically stronger.

01:05:27.430 --> 01:05:30.020
The problem with this
very common theory

01:05:30.020 --> 01:05:33.870
is that in human societies,
and even other ape societies,

01:05:33.870 --> 01:05:38.750
there is no direct correlation
between physical strength

01:05:38.750 --> 01:05:40.710
and social power.

01:05:40.710 --> 01:05:44.400
In human society, for
example, people in their 60s

01:05:44.400 --> 01:05:47.810
usually dominate
people in their 20s

01:05:47.810 --> 01:05:50.390
even though they are
weaker physically.

01:05:50.390 --> 01:05:52.090
Or when you look
at organizations,

01:05:52.090 --> 01:05:55.470
like the Catholic church,
so the pope is not

01:05:55.470 --> 01:05:58.110
the strongest
Catholic in the world.

01:05:58.110 --> 01:06:00.090
And he did not
become pope by going

01:06:00.090 --> 01:06:03.160
go around beating all the
other bishops and cardinals.

01:06:03.160 --> 01:06:05.640
You become pope or
you become president

01:06:05.640 --> 01:06:08.450
by building coalitions
of supporters.

01:06:08.450 --> 01:06:13.240
Social skills are the key for
social power among humans.

01:06:13.240 --> 01:06:17.060
And it's often argued that women
have superior social skills.

01:06:17.060 --> 01:06:19.470
They are better in compromising.

01:06:19.470 --> 01:06:23.040
They are better at understanding
how other people think,

01:06:23.040 --> 01:06:24.470
what other people want.

01:06:24.470 --> 01:06:26.930
Whereas men are much
more self-centered

01:06:26.930 --> 01:06:29.770
and have difficulty
understanding or caring

01:06:29.770 --> 01:06:32.640
about what other
people think and feel.

01:06:32.640 --> 01:06:37.260
So if this is true we should
have got matriarchal societies.

01:06:37.260 --> 01:06:40.925
And among our closest cousins in
nature, the bonobo chimpanzees,

01:06:40.925 --> 01:06:44.370
we indeed find
matriarchal societies.

01:06:44.370 --> 01:06:46.790
So how come in Homo
sapiens, nevertheless

01:06:46.790 --> 01:06:50.300
in most societies in
the last 10,000 years

01:06:50.300 --> 01:06:52.560
women were dominated by men?

01:06:52.560 --> 01:06:55.830
We just don't know at present.

01:06:55.830 --> 01:06:58.790
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] it could
have been a survival strategy.

