01:11:36.980 --> 01:11:39.020
It's really a
question of semantics,

01:11:39.020 --> 01:11:40.470
of how you define things.

01:11:40.470 --> 01:11:42.620
Many people define
religion as belief

01:11:42.620 --> 01:11:46.270
in God or supernatural powers.

01:11:46.270 --> 01:11:48.980
Nobody defines it as
believing irrationality.

01:11:48.980 --> 01:11:51.360
Religious people think
they are very rational.

01:11:51.360 --> 01:11:54.530
They never say, I'm
religious, I'm irrational.

01:11:54.530 --> 01:11:57.550
Maybe a few of them do, but
the vast majority of them

01:11:57.550 --> 01:12:01.180
don't think that religion is
superstition or irrationality.

01:12:01.180 --> 01:12:03.560
Now, if you define
religion as belief in gods,

01:12:03.560 --> 01:12:06.052
then, yes, liberalism
or communism, no,

01:12:06.052 --> 01:12:07.010
they are not religions.

01:12:07.010 --> 01:12:09.870
And certainly data
religion is not a religion.

01:12:09.870 --> 01:12:12.460
But this is a very narrow
definition of religion.

01:12:12.460 --> 01:12:14.270
There have been
religions in history

01:12:14.270 --> 01:12:18.070
in which gods played a very
minor role like Buddhism

01:12:18.070 --> 01:12:19.750
and Confucianism.

01:12:19.750 --> 01:12:21.690
And we still call them religion.

01:12:21.690 --> 01:12:24.830
For me the basic
definition of religion

01:12:24.830 --> 01:12:27.380
is in terms of the
function it plays

01:12:27.380 --> 01:12:29.530
in history and in society.

01:12:29.530 --> 01:12:36.150
Religion gives legitimacy
to human lows and norms

01:12:36.150 --> 01:12:42.510
by hanging on to some super
human power or law of entity.

01:12:42.510 --> 01:12:45.650
We come to people and we say,
you have to behave like this.

01:12:45.650 --> 01:12:48.120
And they ask, why?

01:12:48.120 --> 01:12:50.610
So you don't answer,
because I said so

01:12:50.610 --> 01:12:53.260
or because a couple of
people invented this law

01:12:53.260 --> 01:12:54.470
and now you must obey.

01:12:54.470 --> 01:12:55.890
This won't work.

01:12:55.890 --> 01:12:59.510
You must go to some
super human authority.

01:12:59.510 --> 01:13:02.480
Now there are two kinds
of superhuman authorities

01:13:02.480 --> 01:13:04.690
we find throughout story.

01:13:04.690 --> 01:13:07.600
One kind is gods.

01:13:07.600 --> 01:13:11.320
They are these superior
beings with personalities.

01:13:11.320 --> 01:13:13.200
If you don't do this,
they'll become angry.

01:13:13.200 --> 01:13:14.470
They'll punish you.

01:13:14.470 --> 01:13:16.490
But there is another
option, which

01:13:16.490 --> 01:13:19.420
was common throughout
history and this

01:13:19.420 --> 01:13:22.210
is to turn to natural laws.

01:13:22.210 --> 01:13:25.950
The argument is human laws,
[? the laws ?] of society

01:13:25.950 --> 01:13:27.910
were not invented by humans.

01:13:27.910 --> 01:13:31.660
They reflect the laws of nature.

01:13:31.660 --> 01:13:33.500
Therefore they
are not arbitrary.

01:13:33.500 --> 01:13:35.680
They are not random and
you can't change them.

01:13:35.680 --> 01:13:37.580
You have to follow them.

01:13:37.580 --> 01:13:40.270
So this is the case with
Buddhism and Confucianism.

01:13:40.270 --> 01:13:43.680
This is the case also with
communism or with Nazism.

01:13:43.680 --> 01:13:46.900
The Nazis come and
say, look, it's

01:13:46.900 --> 01:13:50.370
not Hitler that invented this
whole racial theory and then

01:13:50.370 --> 01:13:53.080
that they should be
exterminated and so forth.

01:13:53.080 --> 01:13:54.650
This is the laws of nature.

01:13:54.650 --> 01:13:56.810
Natural selection,
you've read Darwin.

01:13:56.810 --> 01:14:00.460
There are different biological
groups and so forth.

01:14:00.460 --> 01:14:04.300
Now we can say that
the Nazis misunderstood

01:14:04.300 --> 01:14:06.780
Darwin and the
theory of evolution.

01:14:06.780 --> 01:14:11.050
But in their eyes, the laws,
like the Nuremberg Laws

01:14:11.050 --> 01:14:15.760
did not reflect some whim
of Hitler and the party.

01:14:15.760 --> 01:14:19.710
It reflected the
ultimate laws of nature.

01:14:19.710 --> 01:14:22.820
And if we don't
follow these laws

01:14:22.820 --> 01:14:25.650
we will disappear,
like other species

01:14:25.650 --> 01:14:27.390
that have disappeared before us.

01:14:27.390 --> 01:14:30.140
So in this sense I
think that we can

01:14:30.140 --> 01:14:34.000
speak about these ideologies
actually as religions

01:14:34.000 --> 01:14:36.700
because they fulfill
the same function.

01:14:36.700 --> 01:14:42.130
They give legitimacy to
human laws and norms.

01:14:42.130 --> 01:14:47.140
And the last question
was about Gregor Mendel,

01:14:47.140 --> 01:14:50.639
that the church did
contribute, say, to genetics.

01:14:50.639 --> 01:14:51.930
But it's not really the church.

01:14:51.930 --> 01:14:52.864
I'm not sure that--

01:14:52.864 --> 01:14:53.780
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

01:14:53.780 --> 01:14:56.321
YUVAL HARARI: Yeah, I'm not sure
that the pope was very happy

01:14:56.321 --> 01:14:58.470
if he knew what Gregor
Mendel was up to,

01:14:58.470 --> 01:15:00.960
or what would come out of it.

01:15:00.960 --> 01:15:03.510
Which is not the same
as the United States

01:15:03.510 --> 01:15:06.790
financing the Manhattan Project.

01:15:06.790 --> 01:15:10.480
They knew exactly where they
were heading and they got it.

01:15:10.480 --> 01:15:15.940
So I think that there
is a difference there.

01:15:15.940 --> 01:15:21.136
AUDIENCE: So a few kind of
questions dash comments.

01:15:21.136 --> 01:15:29.210
One is what is your
take on, I know

01:15:29.210 --> 01:15:33.240
of at least a myth or
a fact of one society

01:15:33.240 --> 01:15:37.250
that was matriarchal
in history, the Minoan.

01:15:37.250 --> 01:15:43.720
And I wonder if it
actually does end up

01:15:43.720 --> 01:15:49.640
being supported by
historical facts, what

01:15:49.640 --> 01:15:54.677
are the reasons that this
culture kind of vanished?

01:15:54.677 --> 01:15:55.510
That's one question.

01:15:55.510 --> 01:16:00.720
And the other one is with
respect to science fiction,

01:16:00.720 --> 01:16:05.610
not all science fiction
is as you've described.

01:16:05.610 --> 01:16:06.570
And specifically--

01:16:06.570 --> 01:16:07.445
YUVAL HARARI: I know.

01:16:07.445 --> 01:16:08.835
AUDIENCE: No,
specifically as you

01:16:08.835 --> 01:16:12.260
were talking I was thinking
of Heinlein and Asimov

01:16:12.260 --> 01:16:17.870
who exactly have the
stories specifically talking

01:16:17.870 --> 01:16:20.840
about these exact things.

01:16:20.840 --> 01:16:26.120
And I wonder how you think
they would incorporate in

01:16:26.120 --> 01:16:28.912
our future history, so to speak.

01:16:28.912 --> 01:16:29.620
YUVAL HARARI: OK.

01:16:29.620 --> 01:16:32.630
So about the Minoan
culture, I'm not an expert.

01:16:32.630 --> 01:16:36.410
As far as I know, but you
have to check it with experts,

01:16:36.410 --> 01:16:39.130
as far as I know it was for
a time believed that it was

01:16:39.130 --> 01:16:42.690
a matriarchal society,
but no longer.

01:16:42.690 --> 01:16:46.400
Today the archaeological and
the deciphering of the writing

01:16:46.400 --> 01:16:50.690
system show that it was probably
as patriarchal as any other,

01:16:50.690 --> 01:16:54.930
maybe a little less, but it was
still a patriarchal society.

01:16:54.930 --> 01:16:58.430
We have some genuine examples
of matriarchal societies.

01:16:58.430 --> 01:17:01.740
For instance, I think there
is a certain region in China

01:17:01.740 --> 01:17:06.050
in the southwest
of China that there

01:17:06.050 --> 01:17:08.350
is a genuine matriarchal
society there,

01:17:08.350 --> 01:17:10.120
but this is very, very rare.

01:17:10.120 --> 01:17:12.630
The vast majority of
societies and cultures

01:17:12.630 --> 01:17:17.210
known to science in the last
10,000 years were patriarchal.

01:17:17.210 --> 01:17:19.490
About science fiction, yeah,
you're of course right.

01:17:19.490 --> 01:17:22.380
There are many strands
and not all of them

01:17:22.380 --> 01:17:26.705
follow the basic script
that I described,

01:17:26.705 --> 01:17:32.680
like the "Frankenstein" script,
or the "Frankenstein" myth.

01:17:32.680 --> 01:17:39.710
But even in the case of the
writings of Asimov, for me

01:17:39.710 --> 01:17:42.730
the most interesting
tension and connection

01:17:42.730 --> 01:17:47.050
is between biology
and computer science.

01:17:47.050 --> 01:17:50.850
Very often when people
think about the ideas

01:17:50.850 --> 01:17:54.300
that I raised in the
last part of the lecture,

01:17:54.300 --> 01:17:58.010
they give all the importance
to the advances in computer

01:17:58.010 --> 01:18:02.170
science to our ability to create
better and better algorithms

01:18:02.170 --> 01:18:03.760
and computer programs.

01:18:03.760 --> 01:18:05.800
But in my eyes the
real revolution

01:18:05.800 --> 01:18:07.780
is actually from
the life sciences.

01:18:07.780 --> 01:18:10.810
The really big revolution
is when the life sciences

01:18:10.810 --> 01:18:13.280
are telling us that
animals are basically

01:18:13.280 --> 01:18:15.240
biochemical algorithms.

01:18:15.240 --> 01:18:17.220
If they didn't tell
us this then you

01:18:17.220 --> 01:18:20.130
can have all the advances
you want in computer science.

01:18:20.130 --> 01:18:22.425
It won't impinge on humanity.

01:18:22.425 --> 01:18:23.800
You will still
have humans, which

01:18:23.800 --> 01:18:25.258
are something
completely different.

01:18:25.258 --> 01:18:28.750
And all the advances in
robotics and computers,

01:18:28.750 --> 01:18:30.720
OK, we'll have better computers.

01:18:30.720 --> 01:18:33.130
We'll have better robots,
but it won't really

01:18:33.130 --> 01:18:35.720
make much of a difference to us.

01:18:35.720 --> 01:18:40.650
Where it becomes really
amazing and really frightening

01:18:40.650 --> 01:18:42.350
is that once you
realize-- and this

01:18:42.350 --> 01:18:44.370
is a contribution of
the life sciences--

01:18:44.370 --> 01:18:48.090
that actually humans
working in the same way,

01:18:48.090 --> 01:18:51.160
then you can make
the connections.

01:18:51.160 --> 01:18:53.750
And this is the really
frightening stuff.

01:18:53.750 --> 01:18:56.930
This is also why I think
more and more companies

01:18:56.930 --> 01:19:01.000
like Google that started simply
as, in the computer business,

01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:03.830
are moving more and more to
the biotechnology business.

01:19:03.830 --> 01:19:08.655
And then the two industries
are merging into one.

01:19:08.655 --> 01:19:12.080
The most fundamental
idea in this respect

01:19:12.080 --> 01:19:14.550
comes from the life
sciences, which says,

01:19:14.550 --> 01:19:17.440
organisms are algorithms.

01:19:17.440 --> 01:19:22.830
This is the most important,
I think, insight of our age.

01:19:22.830 --> 01:19:24.730
And also the most
important question

01:19:24.730 --> 01:19:27.310
because we don't
have any proof of it.

01:19:27.310 --> 01:19:29.180
Currently, it's just dogma.

01:19:29.180 --> 01:19:35.690
We don't have any explanation
of how any kind of algorithm

01:19:35.690 --> 01:19:38.610
can create subjective
experiences.

01:19:38.610 --> 01:19:41.340
Indeed, in the field
of computers we are,

01:19:41.340 --> 01:19:44.580
as far as I know, we're
not even close to creating

01:19:44.580 --> 01:19:46.900
subjective experiences
in computers.

01:19:46.900 --> 01:19:48.890
It's just a dogma that
people will say, yes.

01:19:48.890 --> 01:19:50.640
It's the same.

01:19:50.640 --> 01:19:53.860
To give another
historical reference, back

01:19:53.860 --> 01:19:56.220
in the 19th century
when they tried

01:19:56.220 --> 01:20:00.560
to understand humans, and the
human mind, and the human soul,

01:20:00.560 --> 01:20:04.670
or whatever you would
like to call it,

01:20:04.670 --> 01:20:07.190
one of the main theories
was that humans were not

01:20:07.190 --> 01:20:08.270
algorithms.

01:20:08.270 --> 01:20:10.850
Humans were steam engines.

01:20:10.850 --> 01:20:13.560
This is the basic
metaphor that stands

01:20:13.560 --> 01:20:17.330
at the basis of
Freudian psychology.

01:20:17.330 --> 01:20:19.520
Humans usually try
to explain themselves

01:20:19.520 --> 01:20:22.340
in terms of the most
sophisticated technology

01:20:22.340 --> 01:20:22.840
of the day.

01:20:22.840 --> 01:20:24.600
Ah, we are like
this because this

01:20:24.600 --> 01:20:26.690
is the most sophisticated
thing I know.

01:20:26.690 --> 01:20:30.290
In 1900, the most
sophisticated machine,

01:20:30.290 --> 01:20:32.400
the most sophisticated
technology,

01:20:32.400 --> 01:20:34.480
which was the basis
for the whole economy,

01:20:34.480 --> 01:20:36.090
was the steam engine.

01:20:36.090 --> 01:20:39.470
So people came and said, ah, the
brain is like a steam engine.

01:20:39.470 --> 01:20:42.570
There are valves and there
are pressures and so forth.

01:20:42.570 --> 01:20:48.120
So even today we say that when
we want to unload our angst,

01:20:48.120 --> 01:20:52.330
like we pick up the telephone
and we release some steam.

01:20:52.330 --> 01:20:56.630
The idea is that the human being
is built like a steam engine.

01:20:56.630 --> 01:20:59.070
It has all these
pressures inside.

01:20:59.070 --> 01:21:01.290
And if you block it
here it goes there.

01:21:01.290 --> 01:21:04.360
And much of Freudian
psychology is built on this.

01:21:04.360 --> 01:21:07.140
So today this sounds
childish and silly.

01:21:07.140 --> 01:21:09.240
Oh, the human being is
like a steam engine?

01:21:09.240 --> 01:21:11.469
We have a much better
technology is the computer.

01:21:11.469 --> 01:21:13.510
So we say, ah, humans are
not like steam engines.

01:21:13.510 --> 01:21:15.120
They are like computers.

01:21:15.120 --> 01:21:18.360
But at present at least
this is just a dogma.

01:21:18.360 --> 01:21:24.920
We don't have the hard
facts to actually prove it.

01:21:24.920 --> 01:21:27.360
